---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { buildChoropleth, fillFor, WIDTH, HEIGHT } from "../lib/geo";
import totals from "../../public/aggregates/totals.json";

const model = buildChoropleth();
const verified = totals.verified;
---

<Base title="Carriers On Notice">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="notice">
      <p>
        The counts on this site are real. They come from public primary
        sources, mostly official consumer arbitration files that name the
        company, and the <a href="/methodology">methodology</a> shows exactly
        how each number is made. The evidence library pages still show sample
        records while we wire them to the live data; those keep a SAMPLE badge
        until then.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h1>Carriers On Notice</h1>

    <p class="count-pill" style="font-size:1.1rem;">
      <strong>{verified.toLocaleString("en-US")}</strong>&nbsp;verified records
    </p>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        This is a public record of how US wireless carriers run device
        promotions, and what customers say happens next. Here is the line we
        hold. Documented facts come from public sources, and each one links to
        that source. Where we offer a read on what those facts add up to, we
        label it as commentary. We never blur the two.
      </p>
      <p>
        Documented fact, for example: federal regulators have taken public
        enforcement actions against wireless carriers over billing practices,
        and those actions are on the public record. Commentary, clearly labeled
        as our read: a pattern of promotion terms that change after signup is
        worth watching closely. The facts are sourced. The read is ours, and we
        say so.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Start here</h2>
    <ul class="card-grid">
      <li class="card">
        <h3>Evidence library</h3>
        <p>Sourced records, each with a citation block you can copy.</p>
        <a class="btn" href="/library">Open the library</a>
      </li>
      <li class="card">
        <h3>Take action</h3>
        <p>Plain steps to file with the FCC or your state attorney general.</p>
        <a class="btn" href="/take-action">See how</a>
      </li>
      <li class="card">
        <h3>Tell your story</h3>
        <p>Share what happened in your own words. You choose to send it.</p>
        <a class="btn" href="/tell">Tell your story</a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The map</h2>
    <p class="prose">
      Wireless billing complaint concentration by state, all carriers, from the
      FCC layer. This preview does not move. The full map, with filters, hot
      spots, and drill down, is one click away.
    </p>

    <a
      href="/map"
      class="map-preview-link"
      aria-label="Open the interactive map. Preview shows a static choropleth of complaint concentration."
    >
      <svg
        class="us-map-preview"
        viewBox={`0 0 ${WIDTH} ${HEIGHT}`}
        role="img"
        aria-label="Static preview of the US complaint concentration map from the FCC complaint dataset. Open the map page for the full data table and interactive version."
      >
        {
          model.states.map((s) => (
            <path
              d={s.path}
              fill={fillFor(s.bin)}
              stroke="var(--border)"
              stroke-width="0.75"
            />
          ))
        }
      </svg>
    </a>
    <p><a class="btn" href="/map">Open the interactive map</a></p>

    <h2>How the numbers work</h2>
    <p class="prose">
      Every public number links to how it is counted. Only corroborated and
      verified primary records feed the public counts. The FCC complaint layer
      has no carrier name field, so it is never shown per carrier. Read the
      <a href="/methodology">methodology</a> for the full rules, and the
      <a href="/corrections">corrections page</a> for anything we have fixed.
    </p>
  </div>

  <style>
    .map-preview-link {
      display: block;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      background: var(--surface);
      padding: 0.5rem;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
    .us-map-preview {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
    }
  </style>
</Base>
